This paper proposes a new policy gradient estimator for reinforcement learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on tasks with binary action space, which suggests a focus on discrete optimization. The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.RO (Robotics).
